<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-12-19"><hi rend="italic">December 19,
                                    1894</hi></date>. (Received Dec. 20.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have been orally informed that the flour claims will be paid, but that
                            it is necessary for Congress to make appropriation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>